## Summary

This walkthrough documents the comprehensive documentation audit, GitHub sync, and premium logo creation for the `zget` project following the "Minimalist Portal" pivot of January 2026. The final deliverable includes the deployment of the "Silk Gold Ribbon" brand identity.ansforming `zget` into a premium, app-native media archival system optimized for both desktop and mobile high-fidelity preservation.

## Logo Creation & Deployment

### Final Selection: Silk Gold Ribbon (Stacked)

After multiple refinement iterations, the user selected the **Silk Gold Ribbon** design in a Stacked layout as the primary brand identity. This premium 3D asset features a golden silk ribbon twisting through space to form a "Z", with clean "zget" typography underneath.

![Final Logo: Silk Gold Ribbon Stacked](/Users/base/.gemini/antigravity/brain/96534431-eec5-45ce-b60c-0118b51f4eb0/zget_final_silk_stacked_1767569386676.png)

### Deployment

- **Primary Logo**: [src/zget/server/static/icon.png](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/icon.png) (Silk Stacked - full branding)
- **Favicon/Small Icon**: [src/zget/server/static/favicon.png](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/favicon.png) (Standalone ribbon icon)

The logo aligns with the "Minimalist Portal" aesthetic, providing a premium, high-fidelity visual identity for the zget archival engine.

## Key Refinements

### 1. The Minimalist Pivot

- **Clutter Elimination**: Removed redundant video descriptions from the player modal to focus on content.
- **High-Density Metadata**: Implemented a pro-grade technical metadata overlay (Views | Resolution | Codec) with clean visual separators.
- **Natural Aspect Ratios**: The Vault grid now natively respects content dimensions—YouTube landscape and Reels/Shorts verticality are preserved without cropping.

### 2. Pro-Grade Mobile Archival

- **Reliable Downloads**: Re-engineered the media endpoint with aggressive attachment headers and slugified filenames (e.g., `video_title.mp4`).
- **Hidden Anchor Strategy**: Switched to temporary anchor tag execution in the frontend to reliably trigger "Save File" prompts on iOS/Android browsers.
- **Direct Vault Actions**: Added instant download buttons to Vault cards for rapid archival without entering the player.

### 3. Native Architecture

- **Zero-Build UI**: 100% Native Web Components with Shadow DOM. No bundlers or npm dependencies in the final Portal.
- **Shadow DOM Encapsulation**: Complete CSS isolation for predictable styling across any mobile browser.

## Technical Summary

### Documentation & Governance

- **[README.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/README.md)**: Updated with the new "Triad" branding and feature set.
- **[AGENTS.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/AGENTS.md)**: Codified aesthetic standards for future development.
- **[openspec/project.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/openspec/project.md)**: Documented the Minimalist Design Principles.

### Backend Updates

- **[app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py)**: Added `sanitize_filename` slugification and forced `application/octet-stream` headers for downloads.

### Frontend Components

- **[player.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/player.js)**: New minimalist layout with metadata-first hierarchy.
- **[vault.js](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/components/vault.js)**: Integrated natural aspect ratio grid and quick-action buttons.

## Final Verification

- **GitHub Sync**: All changes committed and pushed to [bubroz/zget](https://github.com/bubroz/zget.git).
- **Mobile Audit**: Verified that "Download" buttons correctly trigger file save prompts with human-readable titles.
- **Aesthetic Audit**: Confirmed the high-end, uncluttered feel of the new Portal interface.

